He speaks of "European paradox" Dmitri Peskov, underlining that European leaders "would think about peace and instead speak about preparing for war". The Kremlin spokesman pointed his finger at Emnule Macron's words on French nuclear deterrence calling them "dangerous".
"We leave his statements on a nuclear umbrella for Europe, and they seem pretty dangerous," Peskov said during an interview. Today European countries have to leave their "comfort zone", he added, but they are doing it "aggressively and militaristicly".
